-----------------------------------------------------------
KEY TAKEAWAYS
-----------------------------------------------------------

nc connects your terminal to a remote server. You will use this constantly in CTF challenges.

base64 -d is one of the most common decodings you will encounter in CTFs. Learn to recognise Base64 encoded strings by their appearance.

rev is a simple but useful tool. Reversed text shows up in beginner challenges fairly often.

tr is extremely powerful. It handles character-by-character substitution and can process multiple pairs at once.

ROT13 is self-reversing. If you see it, you do not need a different command to undo it.

Always read the hint carefully. It tells you exactly what transformation was applied and points you toward the right tool.
